1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:11,100
<i> Ma'am, what's this for?</i>

2
00:00:11,233 --> 00:00:12,500
<i> Why are you giving me money?</i>

3
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:13,667
<i> Spy on Marj.</i>

4
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:16,867
<i>I want you to sabotage
whatever Marj does.</i>

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>What is this?
Why is this so salty?</i>

6
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:20,667
<i>It's a dose
of your own medicine.</i>

7
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:21,900
<i> You're useless!</i>

8
00:00:22,033 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>Just because their properties
have the Torrecampo name</i>

9
00:00:24,867 --> 00:00:26,033
<i>doesn't mean they'll be easy
to sell.</i>

10
00:00:26,167 --> 00:00:27,200
<i> I don't think so.</i>

11
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,767
<i>We can't expect anything
from management anyway.</i>

12
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:31,200
<i>They can't even fix
their own family.</i>

13
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,300
<i> So this is Nurse Daisy.</i>

14
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>She should've at least talked
to us before hiring a nurse.</i>

15
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:37,767
<i> Mom told me.</i>

16
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:40,733
<i>Why did you take away my say
in taking care of our child?</i>

17
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> So now you know how it feels.</i>

18
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,433
<i>It wouldn't have come to this
if you hadn't interfered.</i>

19
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,167
<i>So, everything that happened
is my fault?</i>

20
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,300
<i> From the very beginning,</i>

21
00:00:48,433 --> 00:00:50,400
<i>all you've brought to this
family is trouble.</i>

22
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:51,633
<i> Where are you going?</i>

23
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:53,400
<i> I just need to rest.</i>

24
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,433
<i> You're leaving Jasmine and me?</i>

25
00:00:54,567 --> 00:00:55,900
<i>I'm staying at my mom's for now.</i>

26
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:58,300
<i>Don't come back
once you walk out that door.</i>

27
00:00:58,433 --> 00:00:59,767
<i> Thea acts all nice.</i>

28
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:00,733
<i> Pretends to be sweet,</i>

29
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:02,400
<i>but she's totally fake
underneath.</i>

30
00:01:11,267 --> 00:01:14,133
Mom.

31
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:18,133
Mom, I'm tired.

32
00:01:18,267 --> 00:01:20,233
I can't handle this anymore.

33
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,933
Marj.

34
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:32,200
It's okay, sweetheart.

35
00:01:32,333 --> 00:01:33,900
Calm down.

36
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,400
Your brother and I are
here for you, Marj.

37
00:01:46,067 --> 00:01:47,300
Sis...

38
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:51,033
Stop crying.

39
00:01:52,067 --> 00:01:55,667
I don't like seeing you cry.

40
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:02,333
I love you, Marj.

41
00:02:08,333 --> 00:02:09,567
Sorry, Jobert.

42
00:02:11,067 --> 00:02:13,033
I'm sad not just because...

43
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:17,400
my child is sick.

44
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:22,567
It feels like my whole family
is falling apart.

45
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:26,767
Everything's falling apart.

46
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,333
Marj...

47
00:02:30,233 --> 00:02:31,033
Sweetheart.

48
00:02:32,033 --> 00:02:33,200
You're just exhausted.

49
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,300
And you have every right to be.

50
00:02:38,033 --> 00:02:39,067
Mom...

51
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,333
It just feels so heavy.

52
00:03:57,533 --> 00:03:58,433
I'm in.

53
00:04:00,067 --> 00:04:00,967
Great.

54
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,267
Great decision.

55
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:05,600
I have a feeling
this partnership

56
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:07,633
is going to be perfect.

57
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:09,533
I think I'm the only one
who really sees your worth

58
00:04:09,667 --> 00:04:10,967
and what you're capable of.

59
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:13,300
Yeah, okay.
Enough with the sales talk.

60
00:04:13,433 --> 00:04:14,700
I've already made up my mind.

61
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:15,800
I said yes, didn't I?

62
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,600
So tell me, Edward...

63
00:04:20,767 --> 00:04:22,300
What made you change your mind?

64
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:24,633
I'm tired of forcing my way
into my dad's life.

65
00:04:25,867 --> 00:04:27,333
My dad...

66
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,367
he never treated me like family.

67
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:31,800
And I'm going to do the same.

68
00:04:33,233 --> 00:04:35,467
Paolo's always the perfect
one in his eyes,

69
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,133
no matter what my brother does.

70
00:04:38,133 --> 00:04:39,967
And I want to prove to them
that he's wrong.

71
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,333
Well...

72
00:04:44,067 --> 00:04:45,767
I guess we both want
the same thing.

73
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,467
Welcome aboard, Mr. Torrecampo.

74
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:22,767
Sir, do you need anything else?

75
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:25,367
I'm good.

76
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:26,633
You can go.

77
00:05:26,767 --> 00:05:28,200
I'll lock up my office myself.

78
00:05:28,333 --> 00:05:29,833
Okay, sir. Good night.

79
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,200
So the rumor is true.

80
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:13,667
Your real wife is this office.

81
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,567
Hi, sweetheart, did you take
your supplements?

82
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:28,667
Yes, Mom.

83
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,100
Nurse Daisy just gave them
to me.

84
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:32,100
<i> Okay.</i>

85
00:06:32,233 --> 00:06:35,200
<i>Jasmine, just call or message me
anytime</i>

86
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:37,167
if something hurts, okay?

87
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:40,967
Sweetheart, can you call me
before you go to sleep?

88
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:43,700
Please?

89
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,700
I love you.

90
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:47,833
Love you, Mom.

91
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:06,933
Sis, do you miss Baby Jasmine?

92
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:09,900
Of course.

93
00:07:12,233 --> 00:07:15,767
Then why don't you go home?

94
00:07:15,933 --> 00:07:19,667
Baby Jasmine and Good Brother
miss you.

95
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:32,533
Marj, I hope you don't get mad
at me, okay?

96
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:36,633
But I kind of understand Paolo.

97
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,633
Maybe he got hurt

98
00:07:40,767 --> 00:07:44,967
because it felt like you took
away his right as a father

99
00:07:45,100 --> 00:07:49,867
when you decided to take Jasmine
abroad on your own.

100
00:07:52,533 --> 00:07:54,333
Mom, I accept that.

101
00:07:55,533 --> 00:07:57,200
I already apologized.

102
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:58,600
I've owned up to it.

103
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:00,667
But why did he still
have to do that?

104
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:02,033
For what?

105
00:08:02,167 --> 00:08:04,167
So we're even?

106
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,867
Is that it?

107
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,367
Marj, it's not like that.

108
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,367
This isn't about getting even.

109
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:12,900
The guard said you've
been here for hours.

110
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:15,000
Everyone else already went home,

111
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,933
but you're still here
at the office.

112
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:24,800
Is this your safe space now
instead of our house?

113
00:08:26,900 --> 00:08:28,067
Well...

114
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,600
you are the CEO.

115
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:35,700
There are no cameras here.

116
00:08:38,567 --> 00:08:41,833
You can do whatever you want.

117
00:08:41,967 --> 00:08:45,700
Marj, the problem
is you're both hurt.

118
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:49,567
You're both carrying
all this resentment.

119
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:56,967
Sometimes in a relationship,

120
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:59,467
someone has to try
to understand.

121
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:06,233
Not to lose, but to finally
end the pain.

122
00:09:09,233 --> 00:09:10,733
Marj...

123
00:09:10,867 --> 00:09:14,000
maybe you should just go home.

124
00:09:19,367 --> 00:09:25,533
Don't let this destroy
what you and Paolo have.

125
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:28,333
Don't let it break your family.

126
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,667
Can you just leave me alone?

127
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,900
It's not like you ever ask me
to stay.

128
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:53,533
Relax, Paolo.

129
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,467
I just don't want you
to be alone.

130
00:09:59,700 --> 00:10:01,900
You've been going through a lot
lately.

131
00:10:06,733 --> 00:10:08,667
Can you please just get out?

132
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,000
Get out!

133
00:10:14,367 --> 00:10:16,433
Why do you always push me away?

134
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:19,133
I just want to help you.

135
00:10:19,267 --> 00:10:22,067
I hate seeing you like this.

136
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,033
Paolo, I care about you.

137
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,567
And I'm different.

138
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:30,433
I'm not like your wife,
who can just ignore you.

139
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:33,633
You know it yourself...

140
00:10:35,633 --> 00:10:37,767
I'm nothing like her.

141
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:50,600
Stop!

142
00:10:52,167 --> 00:10:53,233
Fine.

143
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:55,167
Is that what you want, huh?

144
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,933
What do you really want?

145
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:58,367
Just tell me.

146
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:02,567
However you want it,
however far you want to go.

147
00:11:03,233 --> 00:11:04,367
I'll do it.

148
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:06,533
Touch me.

149
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,533
You've got me, Paolo.

150
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:11,300
You're in control now.

151
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:13,700
Go ahead.

152
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,033
Do whatever you want.

153
00:11:26,333 --> 00:11:27,500
So, I guess...

154
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,000
you really don't want me.

155
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:36,233
I won't force myself
where I'm not wanted.

156
00:12:01,133 --> 00:12:03,267
Is this what you want?

157
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:05,200
Someone who doesn't
ask questions?

158
00:12:05,333 --> 00:12:06,533
Someone who just follows?

159
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,333
Okay. Is this what you want?

160
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:22,767
Marj...

161
00:13:24,867 --> 00:13:28,833
Are you waiting for him?

162
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:32,133
Hoping your husband will come
and get you

163
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,800
so you can fix things?

164
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:40,000
Maybe you're right, Mom.

165
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:43,233
I was at fault, too.

166
00:13:45,333 --> 00:13:48,233
I was so focused on Jasmine

167
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:52,333
that I didn't even notice
I was neglecting my husband.

168
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:02,600
Mom...

169
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,733
I just didn't want
to lose my child.

170
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:10,900
But I don't want
to lose my husband either.

171
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,600
So...

172
00:14:18,133 --> 00:14:19,200
I'm going to fix this.

173
00:14:22,567 --> 00:14:24,100
I don't want Jasmine
to go through

174
00:14:24,233 --> 00:14:26,000
what I went through before.

175
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,833
To have a broken family.

176
00:14:31,233 --> 00:14:32,600
That's why I'm going home.

177
00:14:34,767 --> 00:14:36,000
I'm fixing this.

178
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,000
It doesn't have to end here,
Paolo.

179
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:15,900
It doesn't have
to mean anything.

180
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:23,533
That's what you said before,
too.

181
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,200
Yet here we are.

182
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,533
Last time,

183
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:31,933
we even ended up having
a strong, healthy baby girl

184
00:15:32,067 --> 00:15:33,467
named Ashley.

185
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:38,700
So imagine what else
we could build together.

186
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:42,267
Thea...

187
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,333
This is just sex.

188
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,733
No labels.

189
00:15:49,767 --> 00:15:50,733
No drama.

190
00:15:52,367 --> 00:15:54,667
I don't want to destroy
my family.

191
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,467
They're still my priority.

192
00:15:58,533 --> 00:15:59,633
Of course!

193
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:00,733
Same here.

194
00:16:03,767 --> 00:16:07,833
So is this really the last time?

195
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:10,667
For the second time around?

196
00:16:12,733 --> 00:16:14,567
Last call?

197
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:22,533
You know what?

198
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:30,200
Why end something good?

199
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,433
We can just keep it discreet.

200
00:16:38,767 --> 00:16:40,467
We can just stop...

201
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:43,033
when we no longer want it.

202
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,067
Right?

203
00:17:23,967 --> 00:17:24,800
Love?

204
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,133
Love, let's make up.

205
00:17:33,133 --> 00:17:34,433
Let's fix this.

206
00:17:34,567 --> 00:17:36,300
Our child needs us.

207
00:17:38,233 --> 00:17:40,000
You were the one who left.

208
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,533
I didn't ask you to leave,
right?

209
00:17:41,667 --> 00:17:44,700
Sorry, I just really needed
some space.

210
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,067
Marj, it's okay.

211
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:49,767
Maybe what you did was right.

212
00:17:49,933 --> 00:17:50,800
We needed that.

213
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,967
You want to talk about it?

214
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,400
Nah.

215
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:56,500
I'm okay.

216
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,000
Let's just put this behind us.

217
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:01,833
Okay?

218
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,400
Love?

219
00:18:06,433 --> 00:18:07,367
I'm just going to take a shower.

220
00:18:50,333 --> 00:18:51,333
You're home late.

221
00:18:57,100 --> 00:19:01,333
I just had something important
to take care of at the office.

222
00:19:09,633 --> 00:19:10,833
Don't worry.

223
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:13,400
Soon...

224
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:16,367
you won't need that job anymore.

225
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,433
Everything's about to change.

226
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:31,567
Hon...

227
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:34,933
I found a job.

228
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,067
Consultant.

229
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,267
It pays really well.

230
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:44,200
Soon, we can start fresh.

231
00:19:55,367 --> 00:19:56,333
Let's celebrate?

232
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:43,900
Do you need something?

233
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:46,967
So...

234
00:20:47,100 --> 00:20:47,933
you're back.

235
00:20:48,967 --> 00:20:50,400
Yeah, I'm back.

236
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:52,633
News travels fast in this house.

237
00:20:52,767 --> 00:20:54,500
I was only gone for a day.

238
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:58,733
Well, a lot can happen in a day.

239
00:21:00,067 --> 00:21:01,500
Why?

240
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:02,933
Are you disappointed?

241
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:06,967
Did you think
I wasn't coming back?

242
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,167
Paolo and I worked things out.

243
00:21:09,333 --> 00:21:12,533
Tell whoever's been gossiping to
you that everything between us

244
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:13,767
is going to be fine.

245
00:21:14,967 --> 00:21:15,933
You sure about that?

246
00:21:17,467 --> 00:21:18,733
You know...

247
00:21:18,867 --> 00:21:26,600
sometimes, someone sick or old
suddenly seems okay,

248
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:29,233
but it turns out
it's just a final burst.

249
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,233
What are you talking about?

250
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:37,933
Sometimes you think
they're getting better,

251
00:21:38,067 --> 00:21:41,167
but it's really just their
last bit of strength

252
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,700
before they completely collapse.

253
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,267
So, Marj...

254
00:21:47,167 --> 00:21:49,300
enjoy while it lasts.

255
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:07,633
When I come in,
first, I sign the logbook.

256
00:22:07,767 --> 00:22:10,867
Second, I scan my ID.

257
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:16,300
Third, I go straight
to the photocopy room.

258
00:22:16,467 --> 00:22:20,333
I shouldn't leave that floor.

259
00:22:20,467 --> 00:22:25,933
And no talking to people
unless it's necessary.

260
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:28,200
Lunch break at 12:00.

261
00:22:28,333 --> 00:22:30,567
I'm off at 5:00.

262
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:31,800
Very good!

263
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,733
That's my smart boy.

264
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:37,967
If there's a problem
with the machine,

265
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:40,967
I'll call Supervisor Glenn.

266
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,167
No panicking.

267
00:22:42,300 --> 00:22:43,333
That's right.

268
00:22:43,467 --> 00:22:46,233
No panicking.

269
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:48,300
Just relax, one step at a time.

270
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:49,467
Breathe, sweetheart.

271
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,633
Stay calm, okay?

272
00:22:50,767 --> 00:22:51,967
Yes, Mom.

273
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:53,600
I won't panic.

274
00:22:53,733 --> 00:22:54,733
Just behave.

275
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:56,067
Yes, behave.

276
00:22:56,200 --> 00:22:56,700
Let's go.

277
00:22:56,833 --> 00:22:58,033
Hi, Uncle Greg!

278
00:22:58,167 --> 00:22:59,833
Evelyn.

279
00:22:59,967 --> 00:23:03,533
I knew I'd find you here
this early.

280
00:23:07,133 --> 00:23:09,733
Do you need something?

281
00:23:09,867 --> 00:23:11,800
Is this really your agenda
for today?

282
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:14,367
To ruin my day again?

283
00:23:16,967 --> 00:23:17,900
Jade...

284
00:23:35,067 --> 00:23:36,333
Could you please get the butter?

285
00:23:36,467 --> 00:23:37,767
- Sure, Ma'am.
- It's Paolo's favorite.

286
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,267
- Okay.
- Thank you.

287
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:48,267
Morning, love.

288
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:52,200
I made your favorite.

289
00:23:52,833 --> 00:23:54,200
Oscar's waiting for me.

290
00:23:58,667 --> 00:23:59,667
Let me pack it for you.

291
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,700
Just a second.

292
00:24:02,233 --> 00:24:03,200
Good morning.

293
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:17,000
Good morning.

294
00:24:18,467 --> 00:24:19,700
Good morning, Paolo.

295
00:24:25,267 --> 00:24:26,000
Love!

296
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:28,400
Take care.

297
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,600
You know, Marj...

298
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:42,267
Sometimes I feel like it's not
just Jasmine's body

299
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:45,967
that needs nutrients
in this house.

300
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:56,900
Maybe it won't just be
Jasmine's blood you need

301
00:24:57,033 --> 00:24:58,567
to get checked on your next
hospital visit.

302
00:25:04,133 --> 00:25:05,300
Just saying.

303
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:11,667
When the body's weak,
it's more vulnerable to viruses.

304
00:25:13,500 --> 00:25:15,333
The same goes for relationships,
right?

305
00:25:29,933 --> 00:25:32,200
What I asked you to do
was simple, Edward.

306
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,667
So why hasn't anything
happened yet?

307
00:25:35,833 --> 00:25:37,133
It's not that easy.

308
00:25:37,267 --> 00:25:39,900
What you're asking me
to do isn't simple.

309
00:25:40,033 --> 00:25:41,367
Edward?

310
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:42,967
What are you doing here?

311
00:25:43,100 --> 00:25:44,433
Hon, where are you?

312
00:25:44,567 --> 00:25:46,300
I'm with...

313
00:25:46,433 --> 00:25:47,033
Lalaine.

314
00:25:47,167 --> 00:25:49,233
Lalaine and the girls.

315
00:25:49,367 --> 00:25:51,133
What?

316
00:25:51,267 --> 00:25:52,067
You sure about that?

317
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:57,100
Looks like you've
had a stressful day.

318
00:25:57,233 --> 00:25:59,533
We're still having a hard time
moving the units

319
00:25:59,667 --> 00:26:01,133
of the Menagerie Manor.

320
00:26:01,267 --> 00:26:03,533
Just relax.

321
00:26:03,667 --> 00:26:09,300
Let me make it up to you
for our fight last time.

322
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:14,767
Paolo!

323
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:15,800
Paolo!

324
00:26:15,933 --> 00:26:16,867
Paolo, wait!

325
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:17,867
Paolo!

326
00:26:19,633 --> 00:26:20,533
What?

327
00:26:20,667 --> 00:26:21,667
You're like a different person.

328
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,433
You're hurting me!

329
00:26:23,567 --> 00:26:25,100
What's going on with you?
